  correct_answer = 'B',
  explanation = 'The finding is significant because it suggests that efficiency is not the only factor that influences user adoption. The study shows that people are more likely to use the new technology if they have been exposed to it, even if it is less efficient than the old technology. This suggests that other factors, such as familiarity and comfort, can also play a role in user adoption. The passage states that "The study found that people who had not been exposed to the new technology were more likely to avoid using it, even if i…", which is the textual anchor for eliminating weaker choices. Choice B is correct because it aligns with that evidence: It suggests that efficiency is not the only factor that influences user adoption.. Each incorrect option either contradicts a explicit detail, imports information not present in the text, or answers a different question than the one asked.',
